title: Google\Cloud\Dataflow\V1beta3\KeyRangeLocation
name: KeyRangeLocation
description:
Location information for a specific key-range of a sharded computation.

Currently we only support UTF-8 character splits to simplify encoding into JSON.

Generated from protobuf message google.dataflow.v1beta3.KeyRangeLocation

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.delivery_endpoint
params.description: The physical location of this range assignment to be used for streaming computation cross-worker message delivery.

params.name: data.data_disk
params.description: The name of the data disk where data for this range is stored. This name is local to the Google Cloud Platform project and uniquely identifies the disk within that project, for example "myproject-1014-104817-4c2-harness-0-disk-1".

params.name: data.deprecated_persistent_directory
params.description: DEPRECATED. The location of the persistent state for this range, as a persistent directory in the worker local filesystem.
